de.uni.bamberg.wiai.minf.forflow.datagenerator.model.datastructure
Class ArtefactFactory

java.lang.Object
  de.uni.bamberg.wiai.minf.forflow.datagenerator.model.datastructure.ArtefactFactory

public class ArtefactFactory
extends java.lang.Object

ArtefactFactory class uses the Factory pattern to create data structure objects.

Factories handle the details of object creation. That means, this class has the job of creating objects related to Artefacts.

Please use for object creation the static methods. It won't be possible to use the constructor.

Apr/07/09

createFacetSimplified

public static final FacetSimplified createFacetSimplified()
creates a new and empty FacetSimplified object. This kind uses a sub-set of the whole meta attribute class and is used to do a special kind of job. If you want to have full functionality, please use MetaAttribute class instead.

Returns:

createDataType

public static final DataType createDataType(java.lang.String dataType)
creates an data type object. It can hold all primitive types and some pre-defined complex ones, like String or Date.

To model other complex data types modeled by programmers, any name can be used. But those are not considered in test data generation.

Returns:
data type object
